          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
          "date": "2026-03-25 00:46:03.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
          "date": "2026-03-25 00:46:03.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-19403 utils: prefer ioctl() in llapi_name2dev()",
        "message": "LU-19403 utils: prefer ioctl() in llapi_name2dev()\n\nGenerating the full device list via Netlink in YAML format, then\nwalking the full YAML device list in userspace to find the matching\ndevice name and extract the number is pure overhead.\n\nPrefer to call ioctl(OBD_IOC_NAME2DEV) to directly look up the device\nname in the kernel to get the device number, which does a hash lookup.\nOnly fall back to Netlink/YAML if that doesn't work for some reason.\n\nThis reduces time to look up a device number from 11281us to 862us,\neven on a small system (2MDT+5OST), and significantly more on a\nsystem with more OSTs and MDTs.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nChange-Id: I019ee4a846888fb1e48de963754084c3c353f305\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
